The paper deals with approximate distance oracles for planar graphs, which is a topic in graph algorithms and data structures. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves analyzing the space and query time complexity of the proposed algorithm, which falls under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper presents an improvement over previous results, which could be considered as a contribution to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
